SIMPLE: guile
RECORDS: 2

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Guile
<hw>Guile</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>guile</ets>,
<ets>gile</ets>, OF. <ets>guile</ets>; of German origin, and the same
word as E. <ets>wile</ets>. See <er>Wile</er>.]</ety> <def>Craft;
deceitful cunning; artifice; duplicity; wile; deceit;
treachery.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Behold an Israelite indeed, in whom is no <qex>guile</qex>.</q>
<rj><qau>John i. 47.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>To wage by force or <qex>guile</qex> eternal war.</q>
<rj><qau>Milton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guile</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Guile
<hw>Guile</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[OF. <ets>guiler</ets>. See
<er>Guile</er>, <pos>n.</pos>]</ety> <def>To disguise or conceal; to
deceive or delude.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>
<rj><au>Spenser.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Guileful</ent>⟦br⟧
